before in my entire life.

00:02:16.690 --> 00:02:21.400 align:middle line:84%
And I got them all over my face,
like even up under my eyes,

00:02:21.400 --> 00:02:23.470 align:middle line:90%
in my mouth, and down my throat.

00:02:23.470 --> 00:02:27.130 align:middle line:84%
And that was just
a representation

00:02:27.130 --> 00:02:28.700 align:middle line:90%
of what was going on inside me.

00:02:28.700 --> 00:02:29.500 align:middle line:90%
>> Sure.

00:02:29.500 --> 00:02:30.300 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:02:30.300 --> 00:02:34.480 align:middle line:84%
>> My immune system was so
low that that's what was

00:02:34.480 --> 00:02:36.380 align:middle line:90%
the manifestation of that.

00:02:36.380 --> 00:02:40.580 align:middle line:84%
And leading up until that
moment I'd landed in hospital,

00:02:40.580 --> 00:02:42.940 align:middle line:84%
I had had all of these little
nudges from the universe

00:02:42.940 --> 00:02:47.140 align:middle line:84%
to kind of stop and slow
down and look after myself,

00:02:47.140 --> 00:02:48.760 align:middle line:90%
but I ignored them.

00:02:48.760 --> 00:02:50.170 align:middle line:90%
So the universe is like, right?

00:02:50.170 --> 00:02:52.690 align:middle line:84%
We're just going to
put you in hospital

00:02:52.690 --> 00:02:56.550 align:middle line:84%
and make you stop
and make you look.

00:02:56.550 --> 00:03:00.430 align:middle line:84%
And when I ended up in
hospital, this is back in 2010,

00:03:00.430 --> 00:03:02.650 align:middle line:84%
and it was the darkest
and hardest point

00:03:02.650 --> 00:03:04.030 align:middle line:90%
in my entire life.

00:03:04.030 --> 00:03:06.790 align:middle line:84%
And I felt I was,
at the time, I was

00:03:06.790 --> 00:03:08.110 align:middle line:90%
living on my friend's couch.

00:03:08.110 --> 00:03:09.710 align:middle line:90%
I had no money.

00:03:09.710 --> 00:03:11.220 align:middle line:90%
I was sleeping on her couch.

00:03:11.220 --> 00:03:14.750 align:middle line:84%
I had no idea what I
wanted to do with my life.

00:03:14.750 --> 00:03:15.910 align:middle line:90%
I was single.

00:03:15.910 --> 00:03:17.330 align:middle line:90%
And I was very unhappy.

00:03:17.330 --> 00:03:21.040 align:middle line:84%
And I was on anti-depressants
and very, very unwell.

00:03:21.040 --> 00:03:23.890 align:middle line:84%
And even though that
was the darkest point

00:03:23.890 --> 00:03:29.110 align:middle line:84%
in my entire life, there was
this tiny, tiny, tiny glimmer

00:03:29.110 --> 00:03:30.760 align:middle line:90%
of hope.

00:03:30.760 --> 00:03:33.790 align:middle line:84%
And it's almost like I
could finally surrender.

00:03:33.790 --> 00:03:36.160 align:middle line:84%
And this little bit
of hope Inside me

00:03:36.160 --> 00:03:38.692 align:middle line:84%
said, if you sort
yourself out, if you

00:03:38.692 --> 00:03:40.150 align:middle line:84%
sort your health
and your life out,

00:03:40.150 --> 00:03:42.350 align:middle line:90%
you will live an awesome life.

00:03:42.350 --> 00:03:44.765 align:middle line:84%
And my mean girl, which is
that voice inside your head,

00:03:44.765 --> 00:03:45.640 align:middle line:90%
was like, yeah right.

00:03:45.640 --> 00:03:46.440 align:middle line:90%
Whatever.

00:03:46.440 --> 00:03:48.340 align:middle line:90%
That won't happen to you.

00:03:48.340 --> 00:03:50.050 align:middle line:84%
That doesn't happen
to people like you.

00:03:50.050 --> 00:03:53.860 align:middle line:84%
But that was the first time
I followed my intuition.

00:03:53.860 --> 00:03:57.370 align:middle line:84%
And at the time,
one of my friends

00:03:57.370 --> 00:04:00.430 align:middle line:84%
sent me a parcel when
I was in hospital.

00:04:00.430 --> 00:04:02.380 align:middle line:84%
And in that parcel
was Louise Hay's, "You

00:04:02.380 --> 00:04:03.430 align:middle line:90%
Can Heal Your Life."

00:04:03.430 --> 00:04:04.270 align:middle line:90%
>> Cool.

00:04:04.270 --> 00:04:08.860 align:middle line:84%
>> And that was the door
that was opened to me to this

00:04:08.860 --> 00:04:10.900 align:middle line:84%
personal development,
spirituality,

00:04:10.900 --> 00:04:13.090 align:middle line:90%
holistic health world.

00:04:13.090 --> 00:04:17.050 align:middle line:84%
And I read this book just
like light bulbs going off,

00:04:17.050 --> 00:04:18.579 align:middle line:84%
light bulb, light
bulb, light bulb.

00:04:18.579 --> 00:04:21.800 align:middle line:84%
And I was like, oh my
god, there is another way.

00:04:21.800 --> 00:04:23.620 align:middle line:84%
The way I had been
taught and the way

00:04:23.620 --> 00:04:27.850 align:middle line:84%
I'd been living my life with
fear as my driving force,

00:04:27.850 --> 00:04:30.820 align:middle line:84%
there was another way that
was being exposed to me.

00:04:30.820 --> 00:04:34.120 align:middle line:84%
And from there, it
was so exciting.

00:04:34.120 --> 00:04:37.240 align:middle line:84%
I dove headfirst
into this world,

00:04:37.240 --> 00:04:40.900 align:middle line:84%
and I read every book I could
get my hands on from Deepak

00:04:40.900 --> 00:04:45.220 align:middle line:84%
Chopra, Marianne Williamson,
Eckhart Tolle, Bruce

00:04:45.220 --> 00:04:47.680 align:middle line:90%
Lipton, Demartini.

00:04:47.680 --> 00:04:51.310 align:middle line:84%
And I just became
obsessed with this world.

00:04:51.310 --> 00:04:54.310 align:middle line:84%
I studied holistic
health coaching.

00:04:54.310 --> 00:04:57.170 align:middle line:84%
I studied life coaching,
yoga teacher training,

00:04:57.170 --> 00:05:00.040 align:middle line:90%
AcuEnergetics, meditation.

00:05:00.040 --> 00:05:05.440 align:middle line:84%
And I just fully immersed
myself in this holistic wellness

00:05:05.440 --> 00:05:06.440 align:middle line:90%
space.

00:05:06.440 --> 00:05:10.490 align:middle line:84%
And the reason I did that was
because I started to feel good.

00:05:10.490 --> 00:05:13.630 align:middle line:84%
And I started to come off
all of these medications.

00:05:13.630 --> 00:05:15.410 align:middle line:84%
And when I was in
hospital, the doctors

00:05:15.410 --> 00:05:19.920 align:middle line:84%
plunked this tray full of
drugs in front of me and said,

00:05:19.920 --> 00:05:22.640 align:middle line:84%
you have to take these
antidepressants, antivirals,

00:05:22.640 --> 00:05:25.580 align:middle line:90%
antibacterials, anti whatever.

00:05:25.580 --> 00:05:27.500 align:middle line:84%
You have to take
these indefinitely.

00:05:27.500 --> 00:05:30.000 align:middle line:84%
And I was like, that's
not good enough for me.

00:05:30.000 --> 00:05:33.050 align:middle line:84%
And I just knew that there
was going to be another way.

00:05:33.050 --> 00:05:36.680 align:middle line:84%
I didn't know logically
what that was.

00:05:36.680 --> 00:05:40.490 align:middle line:84%
But that tiny bit of
hope was just like, no.

00:05:40.490 --> 00:05:42.200 align:middle line:90%
There's got to be another way.

00:05:42.200 --> 00:05:46.880 align:middle line:84%
And I dove completely
headfirst into this world,

00:05:46.880 --> 00:05:50.480 align:middle line:84%
like I said, because I
started to feel good.

00:05:50.480 --> 00:05:52.800 align:middle line:90%
And then this was six years ago.

00:05:52.800 --> 00:05:54.770 align:middle line:84%
And from there,
I started working

00:05:54.770 --> 00:05:58.320 align:middle line:84%
one-on-one with women helping
them with their health and life

00:05:58.320 --> 00:05:59.120 align:middle line:90%
goals.

00:05:59.120 --> 00:06:01.370 align:middle line:84%
And I started coaching
them one-on-one.

00:06:01.370 --> 00:06:04.370 align:middle line:90%
I started writing e-books.

00:06:04.370 --> 00:06:07.970 align:middle line:84%
The first e-book I ever wrote
was "12 Steps to Wellness."

00:06:07.970 --> 00:06:10.610 align:middle line:84%
and I just started
sharing on my blog.

00:06:10.610 --> 00:06:13.280 align:middle line:84%
I started being asked to
speak at different things.

00:06:13.280 --> 00:06:16.010 align:middle line:84%
And it has just
snowballed to where

00:06:16.010 --> 00:06:18.500 align:middle line:84%
it is today and having
this beautiful book,

00:06:18.500 --> 00:06:20.930 align:middle line:84%
"Mastering Your Mean
Girl," being now birthed

00:06:20.930 --> 00:06:21.810 align:middle line:90%
into the world.

00:06:21.810 --> 00:06:23.090 align:middle line:90%
>> It's such a beautiful book.

00:06:23.090 --> 00:06:24.590 align:middle line:84%
I mean, there's so
many great photos

00:06:24.590 --> 00:06:25.800 align:middle line:90%
in here and practical tips.

00:06:25.800 --> 00:06:28.790 align:middle line:84%
And one of the first parts
that you talk about in the book

00:06:28.790 --> 00:06:30.560 align:middle line:84%
and really about
this whole story

00:06:30.560 --> 00:06:34.490 align:middle line:84%
is moving from this
approach toward yourself

00:06:34.490 --> 00:06:38.150 align:middle line:84%
and towards life in
general of fear into love.

00:06:38.150 --> 00:06:40.580 align:middle line:84%
And we were talking about
this a little earlier

00:06:40.580 --> 00:06:42.080 align:middle line:90%
before the interview.

00:06:42.080 --> 00:06:43.940 align:middle line:84%
And it's something
that has permeated

00:06:43.940 --> 00:06:46.680 align:middle line:84%
so many different elements
of our lives and society

00:06:46.680 --> 00:06:47.480 align:middle line:90%
in general.

00:06:47.480 --> 00:06:50.660 align:middle line:84%
Tell us a bit about this concept
and how people can practically

00:06:50.660 --> 00:06:52.210 align:middle line:90%
make that transition.

00:06:52.210 --> 00:06:56.450 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, fear is hardwired
into modern society.

00:06:56.450 --> 00:07:01.640 align:middle line:84%
It is shoved down our throats
from a very young age.

00:07:01.640 --> 00:07:05.030 align:middle line:84%
And most of us,
like me, I didn't

00:07:05.030 --> 00:07:06.890 align:middle line:90%
know there was another way.

00:07:06.890 --> 00:07:11.090 align:middle line:84%
I thought fear was the
way to live your life.

00:07:11.090 --> 00:07:12.890 align:middle line:84%
And it wasn't until I
ended up in hospital

00:07:12.890 --> 00:07:15.970 align:middle line:84%
and I was exposed Louise
Hay's work, I was like,

00:07:15.970 --> 00:07:20.030 align:middle line:84%
oh my god, there is
another way to live.

00:07:20.030 --> 00:07:23.150 align:middle line:84%
You don't have to live
a fear-driven life.

00:07:23.150 --> 00:07:25.340 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of people
don't realize that.

00:07:25.340 --> 00:07:26.990 align:middle line:90%
And I didn't realize that.

00:07:26.990 --> 00:07:31.300 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes it takes a
health crisis or a death.

00:07:31.300 --> 00:07:32.100 align:middle line:90%
>> A wakeup call.

00:07:32.100 --> 00:07:34.940 align:middle line:84%
>> A wake up call
for us to realize,

00:07:34.940 --> 00:07:37.850 align:middle line:84%
but it doesn't have
to be that way.

00:07:37.850 --> 00:07:39.860 align:middle line:84%
This could be your wake
up call, this interview.

00:07:39.860 --> 00:07:43.580 align:middle line:84%
Or you could have that
realization on your yoga mat.

00:07:43.580 --> 00:07:46.850 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't have to be something
so dramatic like what I had

00:07:46.850 --> 00:07:49.130 align:middle line:84%
or like what your
dad went through.

00:07:49.130 --> 00:07:54.350 align:middle line:84%
So for me, this
revolutionized the way

00:07:54.350 --> 00:07:56.670 align:middle line:84%
I thought, the way I lived,
the way I did everything

00:07:56.670 --> 00:07:59.930 align:middle line:84%
because I realized that
every area of my life,

00:07:59.930 --> 00:08:01.520 align:middle line:90%
I was doing out of fear.

00:08:01.520 --> 00:08:04.610 align:middle line:84%
So the work I was doing
was from a place of fear.

00:08:04.610 --> 00:08:06.920 align:middle line:84%
The relationships
were from fear.

00:08:06.920 --> 00:08:09.960 align:middle line:84%
I was scared to be alone, so I
held on to these relationships.

00:08:09.960 --> 00:08:11.900 align:middle line:84%
>> How did that work
with the profession,

00:08:11.900 --> 00:08:13.280 align:middle line:90%
the work you were doing?

00:08:13.280 --> 00:08:17.780 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, this, for me, being
an actress and being a dancer,

00:08:17.780 --> 00:08:19.910 align:middle line:90%
that was once my truth.

00:08:19.910 --> 00:08:23.180 align:middle line:84%
And over the years, it
was no longer my truth,

00:08:23.180 --> 00:08:27.350 align:middle line:84%
but I kept on trying to shove
this square peg into a round

00:08:27.350 --> 00:08:29.860 align:middle line:84%
hole and convince
myself that it was.

00:08:29.860 --> 00:08:31.857 align:middle line:84%
I'd been doing this
since I was three.

00:08:31.857 --> 00:08:32.690 align:middle line:90%
I've got to love it.

00:08:32.690 --> 00:08:34.760 align:middle line:84%
I've spent so much
money doing this.

00:08:34.760 --> 00:08:37.159 align:middle line:84%
But it was no longer
lighting me up,

00:08:37.159 --> 00:08:41.340 align:middle line:84%
and I was just trying to
convince myself otherwise.

00:08:41.340 --> 00:08:44.930 align:middle line:84%
And there's lots of people go
to different jobs and careers

00:08:44.930 --> 00:08:46.055 align:middle line:90%
from a place of fear.

00:08:46.055 --> 00:08:47.930 align:middle line:84%
But I didn't know that
you could do something

00:08:47.930 --> 00:08:49.310 align:middle line:90%
that you loved every day.

00:08:49.310 --> 00:08:50.110 align:middle line:90%
Didn't know that.

00:08:50.110 --> 00:08:54.770 align:middle line:84%
>> It's funny that, I guess, you
and I have individually found

00:08:54.770 --> 00:08:56.870 align:middle line:84%
something we're so passionate
about in our lives.

00:08:56.870 --> 00:08:59.450 align:middle line:84%
Me with "Food Matters" and
FMTV and you with the work

00:08:59.450 --> 00:09:00.980 align:middle line:90%
that you do.

00:09:00.980 --> 00:09:03.190 align:middle line:84%
And that has become
a reality for us.

00:09:03.190 --> 00:09:05.720 align:middle line:84%
But had you asked
us both 10 years ago

00:09:05.720 --> 00:09:08.750 align:middle line:84%
that doing something that you're
completely passionate about

00:09:08.750 --> 00:09:11.270 align:middle line:84%
and that you love is
something that you

00:09:11.270 --> 00:09:13.160 align:middle line:84%
can do for the
rest of your life,

00:09:13.160 --> 00:09:15.050 align:middle line:84%
I wouldn't have imagined
it possible either.

00:09:15.050 --> 00:09:16.480 align:middle line:90%
>> No way.

00:09:16.480 --> 00:09:18.710 align:middle line:90%
And earn a living doing it.

00:09:18.710 --> 00:09:21.920 align:middle line:90%
And that isn't taught to us.

00:09:21.920 --> 00:09:24.050 align:middle line:84%
That's not taught
to us in school.

00:09:24.050 --> 00:09:27.030 align:middle line:84%
And it is, it can
be your reality.

00:09:27.030 --> 00:09:30.170 align:middle line:84%
So for me, the career,
the relationships,

00:09:30.170 --> 00:09:33.950 align:middle line:84%
the way I was eating and
not eating was from fear.

00:09:33.950 --> 00:09:38.423 align:middle line:84%
It was, oh, I better
not eat that because I

00:09:38.423 --> 00:09:39.590 align:middle line:90%
don't want to put on weight.

00:09:39.590 --> 00:09:41.447 align:middle line:90%
Or maybe I should limit that.

