and then in her 20s.

00:18:55.890 --> 00:18:57.470 align:middle line:90%
And she got married.

00:18:57.470 --> 00:18:59.870 align:middle line:84%
And she had two
beautiful children.

00:18:59.870 --> 00:19:02.880 align:middle line:84%
And she was married
for 20 years.

00:19:02.880 --> 00:19:06.230 align:middle line:84%
And she realized that
that wasn't her truth

00:19:06.230 --> 00:19:07.940 align:middle line:84%
and that she was
in a relationship

00:19:07.940 --> 00:19:09.540 align:middle line:90%
for the wrong reasons.

00:19:09.540 --> 00:19:11.960 align:middle line:84%
And I said to her, well,
and we spoke about the love

00:19:11.960 --> 00:19:12.770 align:middle line:90%
over fear concept.

00:19:12.770 --> 00:19:14.420 align:middle line:84%
And afterward, I
said to her, when

00:19:14.420 --> 00:19:17.590 align:middle line:84%
did you realize that
this was not your truth?

00:19:17.590 --> 00:19:20.840 align:middle line:84%
And she said, I
knew for 17 years.

00:19:20.840 --> 00:19:24.630 align:middle line:84%
And I was like, that
just blew my mind.

00:19:24.630 --> 00:19:25.940 align:middle line:90%
And I said, how did that feel?

00:19:25.940 --> 00:19:27.523 align:middle line:84%
And she was very
open and very honest.

00:19:27.523 --> 00:19:31.790 align:middle line:84%
And she said, I lived
a lie for 17 years.

00:19:31.790 --> 00:19:34.700 align:middle line:84%
I was convincing myself
that this was my truth,

00:19:34.700 --> 00:19:38.600 align:middle line:84%
that this relationship
was right for me, that you

00:19:38.600 --> 00:19:41.090 align:middle line:84%
had to push through
because relationships

00:19:41.090 --> 00:19:43.680 align:middle line:84%
were hard work because that
was her limiting belief.

00:19:43.680 --> 00:19:44.480 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:19:44.480 --> 00:19:45.280 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:19:45.280 --> 00:19:48.200 align:middle line:84%
And it wasn't until we
started to work together

00:19:48.200 --> 00:19:50.840 align:middle line:90%
that her eyes just opened up.

00:19:50.840 --> 00:19:55.910 align:middle line:84%
And she was like, oh my god,
I didn't come here to suffer.

00:19:55.910 --> 00:19:58.040 align:middle line:84%
I didn't come here
to play the victim

00:19:58.040 --> 00:20:00.500 align:middle line:90%
and to have a tough life.

00:20:00.500 --> 00:20:03.200 align:middle line:84%
And she learned the
love over fear concept,

00:20:03.200 --> 00:20:04.910 align:middle line:90%
and she really freed herself.

00:20:04.910 --> 00:20:07.430 align:middle line:84%
And she was able
to really dial up

00:20:07.430 --> 00:20:09.952 align:middle line:84%
her worthyometer, which is
what I talk about in the book--

00:20:09.952 --> 00:20:10.785 align:middle line:90%
>> Her worthyometer.

00:20:10.785 --> 00:20:11.040 align:middle line:90%
I love it.

00:20:11.040 --> 00:20:12.582 align:middle line:84%
>> --really dial up
her worthyometer,

00:20:12.582 --> 00:20:14.880 align:middle line:84%
really flex her
self-love muscle,

00:20:14.880 --> 00:20:18.720 align:middle line:84%
and have the confidence
to follow her truth.

00:20:18.720 --> 00:20:23.040 align:middle line:84%
And that relationship
dissolved really beautifully.

00:20:23.040 --> 00:20:28.560 align:middle line:84%
There was no dramatic
fights and painful

00:20:28.560 --> 00:20:31.950 align:middle line:84%
because she just did
the work on herself.

00:20:31.950 --> 00:20:34.830 align:middle line:84%
And she was able to resolve
that and move forward

00:20:34.830 --> 00:20:36.540 align:middle line:90%
with as much ease and grace.

00:20:36.540 --> 00:20:37.860 align:middle line:90%
Of course, there was heartache.

00:20:37.860 --> 00:20:39.090 align:middle line:90%
Of course, there was pain.

00:20:39.090 --> 00:20:42.337 align:middle line:84%
I'm not saying that those things
are never going to happen.

00:20:42.337 --> 00:20:43.920 align:middle line:84%
But she was able to
glide through them

00:20:43.920 --> 00:20:48.160 align:middle line:84%
with a lot more grace than if
she didn't have that awareness.

00:20:48.160 --> 00:20:48.960 align:middle line:90%
>> Interesting.

00:20:48.960 --> 00:20:50.820 align:middle line:90%
That's really cool.

00:20:50.820 --> 00:20:52.350 align:middle line:84%
I know, for me
personally, working

00:20:52.350 --> 00:20:55.080 align:middle line:84%
on limiting beliefs has
been such a huge part of me

00:20:55.080 --> 00:20:59.160 align:middle line:84%
transitioning from a
ship's officer and seafarer

00:20:59.160 --> 00:21:00.120 align:middle line:90%
into a filmmaker.

00:21:00.120 --> 00:21:03.330 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I could have had
every story under the sun

00:21:03.330 --> 00:21:04.990 align:middle line:90%
to think that I couldn't do it.

00:21:04.990 --> 00:21:06.060 align:middle line:90%
I have no experience.

00:21:06.060 --> 00:21:07.270 align:middle line:90%
I don't have the background.

00:21:07.270 --> 00:21:09.042 align:middle line:90%
None of my family are in film.

00:21:09.042 --> 00:21:11.250 align:middle line:84%
And yet, our films have been
seen by tens of millions

00:21:11.250 --> 00:21:13.737 align:middle line:84%
of people around the world
because we conquered a lot

00:21:13.737 --> 00:21:14.820 align:middle line:90%
of those limiting beliefs.

00:21:14.820 --> 00:21:17.550 align:middle line:84%
And I'm really a big,
big fan of that work.

00:21:17.550 --> 00:21:18.350 align:middle line:90%
>> Absolutely.

00:21:18.350 --> 00:21:20.940 align:middle line:84%
That is what is
holding people back.

00:21:20.940 --> 00:21:22.710 align:middle line:84%
That's what's
holding people back

00:21:22.710 --> 00:21:24.870 align:middle line:90%
at the start line of their race.

00:21:24.870 --> 00:21:29.400 align:middle line:84%
They're not even willing to
start running because they're

00:21:29.400 --> 00:21:30.720 align:middle line:90%
just so much fear.

00:21:30.720 --> 00:21:33.000 align:middle line:84%
Those limiting
beliefs are so noisy.

00:21:33.000 --> 00:21:34.470 align:middle line:90%
They're just so loud.

00:21:34.470 --> 00:21:37.590 align:middle line:84%
And my whole book
is around mastering

00:21:37.590 --> 00:21:40.560 align:middle line:84%
that voice inside your head
because everyone has an ego.

00:21:40.560 --> 00:21:44.010 align:middle line:84%
And me, 10 years ago, my mean--
and I call her your mean girl.

00:21:44.010 --> 00:21:46.380 align:middle line:84%
You can call her your
bad boy, call him

00:21:46.380 --> 00:21:48.820 align:middle line:84%
your bad boy, or
your ego, or Elvis.

00:21:48.820 --> 00:21:50.070 align:middle line:90%
I don't care what you call it.

00:21:50.070 --> 00:21:53.340 align:middle line:84%
But everyone has that fear
based voice inside their head.

00:21:53.340 --> 00:21:56.070 align:middle line:84%
And when you learn how
to master that voice,

00:21:56.070 --> 00:21:58.950 align:middle line:84%
you will live a
very different life.

00:21:58.950 --> 00:22:00.990 align:middle line:90%
So much more joy and fun.

00:22:00.990 --> 00:22:02.550 align:middle line:84%
And like I said
before, that doesn't

00:22:02.550 --> 00:22:05.610 align:middle line:84%
mean it's going to be rainbows
and butterflies and unicorns.

00:22:05.610 --> 00:22:07.620 align:middle line:84%
There will be
things that happen,

00:22:07.620 --> 00:22:10.020 align:middle line:84%
but you are able to
shimmy through them

00:22:10.020 --> 00:22:13.750 align:middle line:84%
with a lot more grace and
gratitude at the other end.

00:22:13.750 --> 00:22:15.250 align:middle line:84%
>> I can definitely
appreciate that.

00:22:15.250 --> 00:22:17.190 align:middle line:84%
So a question I have
for you, Mel, now

00:22:17.190 --> 00:22:20.370 align:middle line:84%
is that if you think
about life as two paths

00:22:20.370 --> 00:22:23.230 align:middle line:84%
because, generally, that's
how philosophy approaches it.

00:22:23.230 --> 00:22:24.990 align:middle line:84%
You basically have
choices in life.

00:22:24.990 --> 00:22:28.530 align:middle line:90%
But let's say there's two paths.

00:22:28.530 --> 00:22:32.850 align:middle line:84%
Now the path of fear, I would
say, is a very well-lit path.

00:22:32.850 --> 00:22:34.470 align:middle line:90%
It's a very well-paved path.

00:22:34.470 --> 00:22:36.240 align:middle line:84%
And everybody's
walking down that path.

00:22:36.240 --> 00:22:39.360 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you walk into most
cities or most environments

00:22:39.360 --> 00:22:43.530 align:middle line:84%
these days, and people are
living in a fear based state.

00:22:43.530 --> 00:22:47.070 align:middle line:84%
They're fearful about, I
don't have enough money.

00:22:47.070 --> 00:22:48.990 align:middle line:84%
I'm in a relationship
because I need

00:22:48.990 --> 00:22:50.940 align:middle line:84%
to be here to have
that companionship,

00:22:50.940 --> 00:22:52.500 align:middle line:90%
and I don't really love them.

00:22:52.500 --> 00:22:55.230 align:middle line:84%
But I'm scared about getting
out of the relationship.

00:22:55.230 --> 00:22:58.870 align:middle line:84%
Or I'm eating this way because
I don't want to get fat.

00:22:58.870 --> 00:23:00.900 align:middle line:84%
There's always fear
based approach, right?

00:23:00.900 --> 00:23:03.570 align:middle line:84%
And then the love based
approach almost looks a bit

00:23:03.570 --> 00:23:04.920 align:middle line:90%
like a permaculture garden.

00:23:04.920 --> 00:23:07.440 align:middle line:84%
There's weeds growing on
the path a little bit.

00:23:07.440 --> 00:23:09.690 align:middle line:84%
There's lots of flowers,
and it's pretty.

00:23:09.690 --> 00:23:11.730 align:middle line:84%
But it's also a bit
grotty and dirty.

00:23:11.730 --> 00:23:13.830 align:middle line:90%
And there's less people there.

00:23:13.830 --> 00:23:17.250 align:middle line:84%
How do you help people
go down that path

00:23:17.250 --> 00:23:19.020 align:middle line:84%
because it's not
the well-lit path?

00:23:19.020 --> 00:23:20.460 align:middle line:84%
If I think about
medicine as well,

00:23:20.460 --> 00:23:22.770 align:middle line:84%
you've got conventional
medicine and then alternative

00:23:22.770 --> 00:23:24.990 align:middle line:84%
and conventional therapy,
I mean, natural therapies.

00:23:24.990 --> 00:23:28.750 align:middle line:84%
And that was the path that
we had to guide my dad down.

00:23:28.750 --> 00:23:29.620 align:middle line:90%
And it's not easy.

00:23:29.620 --> 00:23:31.920 align:middle line:90%
There's less support.

00:23:31.920 --> 00:23:34.080 align:middle line:84%
You tend to get alienated
unless you're hanging out

00:23:34.080 --> 00:23:36.450 align:middle line:84%
with your tribe and posse like
you do with your little girl

00:23:36.450 --> 00:23:37.240 align:middle line:90%
event and that.

00:23:37.240 --> 00:23:38.730 align:middle line:84%
And some guys come,
I'm sure, hopefully.

00:23:38.730 --> 00:23:39.530 align:middle line:90%
I'll come.

00:23:39.530 --> 00:23:40.650 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:23:40.650 --> 00:23:44.110 align:middle line:84%
>> How do you help people, guide
them down that path of the road

00:23:44.110 --> 00:23:44.910 align:middle line:90%
less traveled?

00:23:44.910 --> 00:23:48.870 align:middle line:84%
Because it is a contrarian
approach to life.

00:23:48.870 --> 00:23:52.320 align:middle line:84%
>> The biggest thing I've
realized is that I can't tell

00:23:52.320 --> 00:23:53.730 align:middle line:90%
people to do it.

00:23:53.730 --> 00:23:56.220 align:middle line:90%
They have to have an experience.

00:23:56.220 --> 00:23:59.370 align:middle line:84%
So the best way
to inspire anyone,

00:23:59.370 --> 00:24:01.200 align:middle line:84%
whether it's your
partner or your children,

00:24:01.200 --> 00:24:03.900 align:middle line:84%
is to be the example and
to give them an experience.

00:24:03.900 --> 00:24:05.640 align:middle line:84%
So there's no point
in me going, Jimmy,

00:24:05.640 --> 00:24:08.713 align:middle line:84%
come down the well-lit path,
like come down the love path.

00:24:08.713 --> 00:24:09.630 align:middle line:90%
It's so much more fun.

00:24:09.630 --> 00:24:11.005 align:middle line:84%
There's rainbows
and butterflies.

00:24:11.005 --> 00:24:12.540 align:middle line:90%
And it's way more fun.

00:24:12.540 --> 00:24:14.940 align:middle line:90%
You could be like, nah.

00:24:14.940 --> 00:24:21.390 align:middle line:84%
But until you have an experience
of what it's like to choose

00:24:21.390 --> 00:24:24.030 align:middle line:84%
love instead of
fear, and you know.

00:24:24.030 --> 00:24:27.180 align:middle line:84%
We all have had those
experiences before.

00:24:27.180 --> 00:24:31.070 align:middle line:84%
Until you really start to
flex your self-love muscle

00:24:31.070 --> 00:24:37.140 align:middle line:84%
and you flex that muscle every
day, it's going to pull you.

00:24:37.140 --> 00:24:39.840 align:middle line:90%
It's like, what charms you most?

00:24:39.840 --> 00:24:42.060 align:middle line:84%
And I'm always like
when I was in hospital,

00:24:42.060 --> 00:24:44.520 align:middle line:84%
that tiny little
glimmer of hope,

00:24:44.520 --> 00:24:46.620 align:middle line:84%
even though it was
like literally this big

00:24:46.620 --> 00:24:49.230 align:middle line:84%
and I couldn't really see
it or contextualize it,

00:24:49.230 --> 00:24:50.280 align:middle line:90%
it charmed me.

00:24:50.280 --> 00:24:52.350 align:middle line:84%
And it just pulled
me and pulled me.

00:24:52.350 --> 00:24:54.840 align:middle line:84%
And it's everything
I do in my life now

00:24:54.840 --> 00:24:57.040 align:middle line:90%
is about what charms me most.

00:24:57.040 --> 00:24:59.670 align:middle line:84%
Does the fear path charm
me more or the love path?

00:24:59.670 --> 00:25:02.270 align:middle line:90%
And sometimes I forget.

00:25:02.270 --> 00:25:04.620 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes my
mean girl is noisy.

00:25:04.620 --> 00:25:06.538 align:middle line:84%
And she tries to take
me down that path.

00:25:06.538 --> 00:25:08.830 align:middle line:84%
And I might start going down
there for like 10 minutes.

00:25:08.830 --> 00:25:10.450 align:middle line:90%
And then I'm like, whoa.

00:25:10.450 --> 00:25:11.890 align:middle line:90%
This is dark down here.

00:25:11.890 --> 00:25:13.280 align:middle line:90%
It stinks.

00:25:13.280 --> 00:25:14.280 align:middle line:90%
I want to go walk down--

00:25:14.280 --> 00:25:15.197 align:middle line:90%
>> Back to the garden.

00:25:15.197 --> 00:25:16.930 align:middle line:84%
>> I want to go
back to the garden.

00:25:16.930 --> 00:25:19.270 align:middle line:84%
And the whole first
section of the book

00:25:19.270 --> 00:25:22.700 align:middle line:84%
is about changing your
internal GPS system.

00:25:22.700 --> 00:25:26.590 align:middle line:84%
So for a lot of us, that
internal GPS is set on fear.

00:25:26.590 --> 00:25:29.820 align:middle line:84%
And we've got to
continue to bring it back

00:25:29.820 --> 00:25:31.162 align:middle line:90%
to get it set on love.

00:25:31.162 --> 00:25:32.620 align:middle line:84%
And there's going
to be things that

00:25:32.620 --> 00:25:34.550 align:middle line:84%
are going to take
us off our path,

00:25:34.550 --> 00:25:35.905 align:middle line:90%
and it's our job to come back.

00:25:35.905 --> 00:25:37.780 align:middle line:84%
And there's going to be
something else that's

00:25:37.780 --> 00:25:39.170 align:middle line:90%
going to take us off our path.

00:25:39.170 --> 00:25:40.795 align:middle line:84%
And we've just got
to keep coming back.

00:25:40.795 --> 00:25:43.060 align:middle line:84%
And the more we practice
it in those moments

00:25:43.060 --> 00:25:46.210 align:middle line:84%
when we really need it,
when shit has hit the fan,

00:25:46.210 --> 00:25:49.720 align:middle line:84%
they're the moments that we have
to practice it not the moments

00:25:49.720 --> 00:25:52.120 align:middle line:84%
when it's all happy
and butterflies.

00:25:52.120 --> 00:25:52.920 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:25:52.920 --> 00:25:54.010 align:middle line:90%
I understand.

00:25:54.010 --> 00:25:58.990 align:middle line:84%
And so it's really great to talk
about the fear path or the love

00:25:58.990 --> 00:25:59.830 align:middle line:90%
path.

00:25:59.830 --> 00:26:01.120 align:middle line:90%
And I've got a really good--

00:26:01.120 --> 00:26:02.530 align:middle line:84%
I've got a better
concept of that now.

00:26:02.530 --> 00:26:04.572 align:middle line:84%
And I think anybody
listening would have a better

00:26:04.572 --> 00:26:05.812 align:middle line:90%
understanding of that now.

00:26:05.812 --> 00:26:07.270 align:middle line:84%
But let's talk
about, what are some

00:26:07.270 --> 00:26:09.520 align:middle line:84%
of the practical ways that
people can integrate this

00:26:09.520 --> 00:26:14.050 align:middle line:84%
into their lives, that
people can help to cultivate

00:26:14.050 --> 00:26:16.690 align:middle line:84%
that love based approach
to themselves and to life

00:26:16.690 --> 00:26:18.440 align:middle line:84%
and in order to be
able to continue

00:26:18.440 --> 00:26:21.970 align:middle line:84%
to attract the situations
and the experiences

00:26:21.970 --> 00:26:23.800 align:middle line:90%
that they want more of?

00:26:23.800 --> 00:26:27.580 align:middle line:84%
Well, I think one of the
best things you can do

00:26:27.580 --> 00:26:30.650 align:middle line:84%
is realize that there is
only ever two choices.

00:26:30.650 --> 00:26:33.990 align:middle line:84%
I think us women, we sometimes
think that, oh, well,

00:26:33.990 --> 00:26:34.790 align:middle line:90%
I could do this.

00:26:34.790 --> 00:26:35.330 align:middle line:90%
And I could do this.

00:26:35.330 --> 00:26:36.520 align:middle line:84%
But then that voice
is saying that.

00:26:36.520 --> 00:26:38.478 align:middle line:84%
But then that voice said
that I should do that.

00:26:38.478 --> 00:26:41.500 align:middle line:84%
And then we sometimes feel
like we have 50 choices.

00:26:41.500 --> 00:26:44.200 align:middle line:84%
But there is only ever
two, love or fear.

00:26:44.200 --> 00:26:46.720 align:middle line:84%
And coming back to that and
reminding yourself of that

00:26:46.720 --> 00:26:48.980 align:middle line:90%
is really, really important.

00:26:48.980 --> 00:26:51.490 align:middle line:84%
So I've got that little
three-step process

00:26:51.490 --> 00:26:54.070 align:middle line:84%
of every time that
fear based voice

00:26:54.070 --> 00:26:58.570 align:middle line:84%
comes up, being aware of it,
gently closing the door on it,

00:26:58.570 --> 00:27:00.040 align:middle line:90%
and then choosing love instead.

00:27:00.040 --> 00:27:04.070 align:middle line:84%
It's a very simple process that
we can apply to everyday life.

00:27:04.070 --> 00:27:04.870 align:middle line:90%
>> Cool.

00:27:04.870 --> 00:27:06.250 align:middle line:90%
So can we do that live now?

00:27:06.250 --> 00:27:06.580 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:27:06.580 --> 00:27:08.110 align:middle line:84%
>> So can I pretend
I'm the fear voice?

00:27:08.110 --> 00:27:08.910 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:27:08.910 --> 00:27:10.420 align:middle line:90%
>> OK, so don't eat that.

00:27:10.420 --> 00:27:12.410 align:middle line:84%
Because if you do it,
you're going to get fat.

00:27:12.410 --> 00:27:16.510 align:middle line:84%
>> OK, so I'm aware that that
is my mean girl or your bad boy.

00:27:16.510 --> 00:27:17.470 align:middle line:90%
So I'm aware.

00:27:17.470 --> 00:27:18.880 align:middle line:90%
That's not my truth.

00:27:18.880 --> 00:27:19.840 align:middle line:90%
That is that voice.

00:27:19.840 --> 00:27:22.900 align:middle line:84%
And your ego speaks
to you in words.

00:27:22.900 --> 00:27:26.940 align:middle line:84%
Your intuition, love
speaks to you in feelings.

00:27:26.940 --> 00:27:29.588 align:middle line:84%
So mainly, anything
that goes on up here--

00:27:29.588 --> 00:27:30.880 align:middle line:90%
>> Like internal dialogue talk.

00:27:30.880 --> 00:27:33.740 align:middle line:84%
>> Internal dialogue
is your ego.

00:27:33.740 --> 00:27:34.540 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:27:34.540 --> 00:27:36.677 align:middle line:84%
>> It's because your
intuition love, it's more--

00:27:36.677 --> 00:27:39.010 align:middle line:84%
I don't know if you've ever
had one of those experiences

00:27:39.010 --> 00:27:42.100 align:middle line:84%
where someone might have
said to you, well, why

00:27:42.100 --> 00:27:43.330 align:middle line:90%
did you book a trip to Bali?

00:27:43.330 --> 00:27:44.580 align:middle line:90%
And you're like, I don't know.

00:27:44.580 --> 00:27:48.130 align:middle line:84%
I just had this feeling like
something was just telling me.

00:27:48.130 --> 00:27:49.530 align:middle line:90%
And it just pulled me.

00:27:49.530 --> 00:27:53.140 align:middle line:84%
And I'm sure everyone's had
an experience like that.

00:27:53.140 --> 00:27:56.050 align:middle line:84%
So that voice pops up
and says, don't eat that.

00:27:56.050 --> 00:27:57.400 align:middle line:90%
So we've become aware of it.

00:27:57.400 --> 00:28:00.880 align:middle line:84%
We know that's our mean
girl or our bad boy.

00:28:00.880 --> 00:28:04.370 align:middle line:84%
And once you know what you
know, you can't unknow it.

00:28:04.370 --> 00:28:05.170 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah, sure.

00:28:05.170 --> 00:28:05.440 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:28:05.440 --> 00:28:06.760 align:middle line:84%
So once the awareness
is there, it's there.

00:28:06.760 --> 00:28:07.560 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:28:07.560 --> 00:28:08.370 align:middle line:90%
You can't pretend.

00:28:08.370 --> 00:28:09.850 align:middle line:90%
You can't be like, yeah, I know.

00:28:09.850 --> 00:28:10.900 align:middle line:90%
That's not my mean girl.

00:28:10.900 --> 00:28:12.730 align:middle line:84%
Unless you have one of
those "Men in Black"

00:28:12.730 --> 00:28:15.220 align:middle line:84%
guns that they like zap
you and erase your memory.

00:28:15.220 --> 00:28:16.100 align:middle line:90%
And I'm pretty sure--

00:28:16.100 --> 00:28:16.900 align:middle line:90%
>> Nobody has that.

00:28:16.900 --> 00:28:18.910 align:middle line:90%
>> --no one has one of those.

00:28:18.910 --> 00:28:21.000 align:middle line:90%
So awareness is key.

00:28:21.000 --> 00:28:25.900 align:middle line:84%
Then with that awareness,
you have an opportunity

00:28:25.900 --> 00:28:27.730 align:middle line:84%
to gently close
the door on that.

00:28:27.730 --> 00:28:29.330 align:middle line:90%
It's not about killing the ego.

00:28:29.330 --> 00:28:30.815 align:middle line:90%
It's not about smashing the ego.

00:28:30.815 --> 00:28:32.440 align:middle line:84%
I know there's a lot
of spiritual texts

00:28:32.440 --> 00:28:34.990 align:middle line:84%
that talk about killing the
ego or smashing the ego.

00:28:34.990 --> 00:28:36.448 align:middle line:84%
>> Ego eradication,
all that, yeah.

00:28:36.448 --> 00:28:37.540 align:middle line:90%
>> It's part of us.

00:28:37.540 --> 00:28:42.040 align:middle line:84%
And I see it as a way to
get back on your path.

00:28:42.040 --> 00:28:44.950 align:middle line:84%
I use my mean girl
as my indicator

00:28:44.950 --> 00:28:46.250 align:middle line:90%
to get back on to love.

00:28:46.250 --> 00:28:47.050 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:28:47.050 --> 00:28:48.100 align:middle line:90%
It's like an element for growth.

00:28:48.100 --> 00:28:49.100 align:middle line:90%
Ego is helping you grow.

00:28:49.100 --> 00:28:49.900 align:middle line:90%
>> Totally.

00:28:49.900 --> 00:28:50.890 align:middle line:90%
>> Turn it around.

00:28:50.890 --> 00:28:53.873 align:middle line:84%
>> It's an opportunity
for growth, exactly.

00:28:53.873 --> 00:28:55.540 align:middle line:84%
So then we gently
close the door on her.

00:28:55.540 --> 00:28:58.060 align:middle line:84%
And then we choose
to reframe it.

00:28:58.060 --> 00:28:59.360 align:middle line:90%
We choose love instead.

00:28:59.360 --> 00:29:01.480 align:middle line:84%
So instead of that
fear based thought

00:29:01.480 --> 00:29:04.330 align:middle line:84%
around what you were eating,
you could say, you know what?

00:29:04.330 --> 00:29:05.770 align:middle line:84%
I'm actually going
to choose this

00:29:05.770 --> 00:29:09.175 align:middle line:84%
because I love my body so
much, and I want to nourish it,

00:29:09.175 --> 00:29:11.800 align:middle line:84%
and I want to look after, and I
want to feel vital and healthy.

00:29:11.800 --> 00:29:15.070 align:middle line:84%
And there's a very
different energy behind it.

00:29:15.070 --> 00:29:16.840 align:middle line:84%
So it's just about
taking yourself

00:29:16.840 --> 00:29:18.820 align:middle line:90%
through those three steps.

00:29:18.820 --> 00:29:20.380 align:middle line:90%
They're very simple.

00:29:20.380 --> 00:29:25.900 align:middle line:84%
But it's not normal
for us because we've

00:29:25.900 --> 00:29:26.740 align:middle line:90%
been conditioned--

00:29:26.740 --> 00:29:27.550 align:middle line:90%
>> To do it the opposite.

00:29:27.550 --> 00:29:28.750 align:middle line:90%
>> --to do it the opposite.

00:29:28.750 --> 00:29:30.583 align:middle line:84%
>> All the advertising
we see on television.

00:29:30.583 --> 00:29:31.383 align:middle line:90%
>> Exactly.

00:29:31.383 --> 00:29:32.920 align:middle line:84%
>> Everything we
see is all about,

00:29:32.920 --> 00:29:34.670 align:middle line:84%
don't do that because
this will happen.

00:29:34.670 --> 00:29:35.470 align:middle line:90%
>> Exactly.

00:29:35.470 --> 00:29:36.790 align:middle line:90%
>> Fear based approach.

00:29:36.790 --> 00:29:38.447 align:middle line:84%
And so one of the
other things I wanted

00:29:38.447 --> 00:29:40.780 align:middle line:84%
to bring up around food because
I think the relationship

00:29:40.780 --> 00:29:42.010 align:middle line:90%
to food is a big thing.

00:29:42.010 --> 00:29:45.258 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of people
struggle with it,

00:29:45.258 --> 00:29:46.300 align:middle line:90%
and they know about that.

00:29:46.300 --> 00:29:47.750 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of people
don't struggle with it.

00:29:47.750 --> 00:29:49.780 align:middle line:84%
But they don't yet know
that it is coming up

00:29:49.780 --> 00:29:51.697 align:middle line:84%
for them in that way,
that they're conditioned

00:29:51.697 --> 00:29:53.140 align:middle line:90%
around food in that way.

00:29:53.140 --> 00:29:57.190 align:middle line:84%
And we were talking a
little bit earlier before

00:29:57.190 --> 00:30:01.810 align:middle line:84%
about how approaching good
food with love and nourishment

00:30:01.810 --> 00:30:04.060 align:middle line:84%
but approaching also if
we don't eat that well,

00:30:04.060 --> 00:30:05.513 align:middle line:90%
approaching that with love.

00:30:05.513 --> 00:30:07.680 align:middle line:84%
Tell me about that because
that's a different thing.

00:30:07.680 --> 00:30:09.390 align:middle line:84%
Because you can
say, I don't want

00:30:09.390 --> 00:30:11.223 align:middle line:84%
to eat that because I
don't want to get fat.

00:30:11.223 --> 00:30:13.490 align:middle line:84%
But then if you do eat
something that is not perfect,

00:30:13.490 --> 00:30:14.290 align:middle line:90%
how do we--

00:30:14.290 --> 00:30:16.800 align:middle line:84%
what's a healthy way
to approach that?

00:30:16.800 --> 00:30:20.130 align:middle line:84%
>> It's about ultimately
being your best,

00:30:20.130 --> 00:30:24.690 align:middle line:84%
being your own best friend,
being the nicest, loving,

00:30:24.690 --> 00:30:29.520 align:middle line:84%
kind person you can be to
yourself in every moment.

00:30:29.520 --> 00:30:33.700 align:middle line:84%
So when you fall down, when
you overeat, like a child.

00:30:33.700 --> 00:30:36.130 align:middle line:84%
You wouldn't go to Hugo,
oh, you stupid idiot.

00:30:36.130 --> 00:30:36.930 align:middle line:90%
Get up.

00:30:36.930 --> 00:30:39.090 align:middle line:84%
You'd be like, up
you get, darling.

00:30:39.090 --> 00:30:40.740 align:middle line:90%
Let's have another go.

00:30:40.740 --> 00:30:44.460 align:middle line:84%
But we speak to
ourselves so horribly.

00:30:44.460 --> 00:30:47.370 align:middle line:84%
Like you would never speak
to your worst enemy the way

00:30:47.370 --> 00:30:50.200 align:middle line:84%
that some of us women
speak to ourselves.

00:30:50.200 --> 00:30:52.540 align:middle line:84%
And I'm not sure if
it's the same for men.

00:30:52.540 --> 00:30:55.770 align:middle line:84%
But some of the dialogue that
us women say to ourselves

00:30:55.770 --> 00:30:58.080 align:middle line:90%
like you would be mortified.

00:30:58.080 --> 00:31:01.620 align:middle line:84%
And you would not speak to
your own worst enemy like that.

00:31:01.620 --> 00:31:04.810 align:middle line:84%
Yet, we allow our mean
girl to do it to us.

00:31:04.810 --> 00:31:06.630 align:middle line:90%
And that has got to stop.

00:31:06.630 --> 00:31:09.600 align:middle line:84%
That berating,
that limiting, fear

00:31:09.600 --> 00:31:11.640 align:middle line:84%
based talk that we
have toward ourself

00:31:11.640 --> 00:31:14.440 align:middle line:84%
is what is holding you
back at the start line.

00:31:14.440 --> 00:31:16.540 align:middle line:84%
And you're never going
to be able to go.

00:31:16.540 --> 00:31:19.120 align:middle line:84%
You're never going to be
able to go on your path.

00:31:19.120 --> 00:31:25.620 align:middle line:84%
So for me, it's about being the
most loving, kind person that I

00:31:25.620 --> 00:31:29.610 align:middle line:84%
can be to myself when I
fall down, when I overeat,

00:31:29.610 --> 00:31:34.250 align:middle line:84%
when I miss my gym session in
the morning, when I stuff up.

00:31:34.250 --> 00:31:37.320 align:middle line:84%
In those moments,
going, you know what?

00:31:37.320 --> 00:31:38.120 align:middle line:90%
That's OK.

00:31:38.120 --> 00:31:39.080 align:middle line:90%
And I love you anyway.

00:31:39.080 --> 00:31:39.390 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:31:39.390 --> 00:31:39.800 align:middle line:90%
I love you.

00:31:39.800 --> 00:31:40.600 align:middle line:90%
You're a rockstar.

00:31:40.600 --> 00:31:41.550 align:middle line:90%
>> You're amazing.

00:31:41.550 --> 00:31:42.350 align:middle line:90%
You're a babe.

00:31:42.350 --> 00:31:44.840 align:middle line:84%
Black give yourself a
little wink in the mirror.

00:31:44.840 --> 00:31:46.800 align:middle line:84%
>> That's the opposite of what
most people would do, though.

00:31:46.800 --> 00:31:47.790 align:middle line:90%
And that's what you're saying.

00:31:47.790 --> 00:31:48.590 align:middle line:90%
>> Totally.

00:31:48.590 --> 00:31:49.970 align:middle line:90%
>> And if you can practice that.

00:31:49.970 --> 00:31:52.230 align:middle line:84%
And what if that feels
uncomfortable in the beginning?

00:31:52.230 --> 00:31:54.723 align:middle line:84%
>> It will feel very,
very uncomfortable.

00:31:54.723 --> 00:31:56.140 align:middle line:84%
>> So like, hey,
I missed the gym.

00:31:56.140 --> 00:31:57.750 align:middle line:84%
But, hey, look in
the mirror and say,

00:31:57.750 --> 00:32:00.030 align:middle line:84%
look, I accept myself
unconditionally right now,

00:32:00.030 --> 00:32:00.510 align:middle line:90%
right?

00:32:00.510 --> 00:32:00.630 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:32:00.630 --> 00:32:02.400 align:middle line:84%
>> And I love myself,
and I'm OK with that.

00:32:02.400 --> 00:32:02.715 align:middle line:90%
I'm cool.

00:32:02.715 --> 00:32:03.515 align:middle line:90%
>> Totally.

00:32:03.515 --> 00:32:06.660 align:middle line:84%
And that's why
affirmations and mirror

00:32:06.660 --> 00:32:09.720 align:middle line:84%
work, which is what Louise Hay
talks about, are so powerful

00:32:09.720 --> 00:32:13.740 align:middle line:84%
and so revolutionized the
way I looked at myself.

00:32:13.740 --> 00:32:15.220 align:middle line:90%
I hated myself.

00:32:15.220 --> 00:32:17.460 align:middle line:90%
I was so hard on myself.

00:32:17.460 --> 00:32:20.700 align:middle line:84%
I was very, very
horrible to myself.

00:32:20.700 --> 00:32:23.340 align:middle line:90%
My internal dialogue was awful.

00:32:23.340 --> 00:32:26.640 align:middle line:84%
And because I didn't know
that there was another way.

00:32:26.640 --> 00:32:30.360 align:middle line:84%
And when I first started doing
affirmations and mirror work,

00:32:30.360 --> 00:32:33.190 align:middle line:84%
I couldn't even look at
myself in the mirror.

00:32:33.190 --> 00:32:36.930 align:middle line:84%
I would just stream and
stream and stream and stream

00:32:36.930 --> 00:32:40.620 align:middle line:84%
because there was so much
pain and so much hurt.

00:32:40.620 --> 00:32:44.490 align:middle line:84%
But I did a lot of
unconditional love

00:32:44.490 --> 00:32:49.210 align:middle line:84%
toward myself and visualizing
myself as a six-year-old.

00:32:49.210 --> 00:32:52.240 align:middle line:84%
And would I speak to my
six-year-old self like that?

00:32:52.240 --> 00:32:53.040 align:middle line:90%
No way.

00:32:53.040 --> 00:32:53.998 align:middle line:90%
>> Of course not, yeah.

00:32:53.998 --> 00:32:55.080 align:middle line:90%
>> No way.

00:32:55.080 --> 00:32:58.710 align:middle line:84%
And yeah, just having
such a loving relationship

00:32:58.710 --> 00:33:01.260 align:middle line:84%
with yourself will
really help you

00:33:01.260 --> 00:33:04.200 align:middle line:90%
achieve what you want in life.

00:33:04.200 --> 00:33:07.710 align:middle line:84%
Because for me, it was like
every time I stuffed up,

00:33:07.710 --> 00:33:08.880 align:middle line:90%
I would beat myself up.

00:33:08.880 --> 00:33:11.650 align:middle line:84%
And now, every time I fall
down, I'm like, great.

00:33:11.650 --> 00:33:12.450 align:middle line:90%
What did I learn?

00:33:12.450 --> 00:33:13.600 align:middle line:90%
How can I grow and evolve?

00:33:13.600 --> 00:33:14.400 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:33:14.400 --> 00:33:16.560 align:middle line:90%
>> It's changing that mindset.

00:33:16.560 --> 00:33:18.060 align:middle line:90%
And that wasn't always0--

00:33:18.060 --> 00:33:20.280 align:middle line:90%
that was not my reality.

00:33:20.280 --> 00:33:21.900 align:middle line:90%
I had to work on that.

00:33:21.900 --> 00:33:23.550 align:middle line:84%
And all of these
self-love things

00:33:23.550 --> 00:33:25.710 align:middle line:84%
we're talking about and
choosing love over fear

00:33:25.710 --> 00:33:31.420 align:middle line:84%
is something that you have
to work on moment to moment

00:33:31.420 --> 00:33:32.220 align:middle line:90%
to moment.

00:33:32.220 --> 00:33:33.900 align:middle line:84%
It's not something
that you can just

00:33:33.900 --> 00:33:36.450 align:middle line:84%
do on Wednesdays and
Saturdays and then expect

00:33:36.450 --> 00:33:37.430 align:middle line:90%
to be enlightened.

00:33:37.430 --> 00:33:38.760 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:33:38.760 --> 00:33:41.700 align:middle line:84%
>> Practicing self-love,
choosing love over fear,

00:33:41.700 --> 00:33:45.060 align:middle line:84%
mastering your mean girl
is a daily moment to moment

00:33:45.060 --> 00:33:46.410 align:middle line:90%
practice.

00:33:46.410 --> 00:33:47.910 align:middle line:84%
And it's something
that the more you

00:33:47.910 --> 00:33:49.410 align:middle line:84%
flex, it's like you
go into the gym,

00:33:49.410 --> 00:33:51.660 align:middle line:84%
the more you do your squats,
the tighter your booty.

00:33:51.660 --> 00:33:52.026 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:33:52.026 --> 00:33:52.760 align:middle line:90%
That's true.

00:33:52.760 --> 00:33:53.560 align:middle line:90%
>> You know?

00:33:53.560 --> 00:33:56.650 align:middle line:84%
So you've just got to flex
that muscle in every moment.

00:33:56.650 --> 00:33:58.100 align:middle line:90%
And it does get easier.

00:33:58.100 --> 00:33:59.280 align:middle line:90%
>> Nice.

00:33:59.280 --> 00:34:02.910 align:middle line:84%
So we've covered a lot of theory
about limiting beliefs, moving

00:34:02.910 --> 00:34:04.800 align:middle line:84%
from fear into love,
and understanding

00:34:04.800 --> 00:34:07.140 align:middle line:84%
that process of how we
connect with ourselves

00:34:07.140 --> 00:34:09.900 align:middle line:84%
and not necessarily
negate the ego

00:34:09.900 --> 00:34:13.860 align:middle line:84%
but use its power in order to
be able to fuel that self-growth

00:34:13.860 --> 00:34:15.389 align:middle line:90%
and self-love.

00:34:15.389 --> 00:34:17.639 align:middle line:84%
But let's land the
plane on this now.

00:34:17.639 --> 00:34:20.969 align:middle line:84%
Let's talk a little bit about
what are some daily rituals

00:34:20.969 --> 00:34:23.420 align:middle line:84%
or practices that I could
introduce into my life

00:34:23.420 --> 00:34:25.170 align:middle line:84%
or that people listening
to this interview

00:34:25.170 --> 00:34:26.837 align:middle line:84%
could introduce into
their life in order

00:34:26.837 --> 00:34:31.020 align:middle line:84%
to be able to really make
it easy for them to build

00:34:31.020 --> 00:34:34.500 align:middle line:84%
up more, like you said,
flexing their muscles

00:34:34.500 --> 00:34:36.300 align:middle line:84%
and build up more
strength in this way.

00:34:36.300 --> 00:34:39.030 align:middle line:84%
>> I think, for me, personally,
the biggest thing has been

00:34:39.030 --> 00:34:40.170 align:middle line:90%
meditation.

00:34:40.170 --> 00:34:43.949 align:middle line:84%
It has radically
changed my life.

00:34:43.949 --> 00:34:45.917 align:middle line:84%
And it doesn't have
to look a certain way.

00:34:45.917 --> 00:34:47.250 align:middle line:90%
You could do guided meditations.

00:34:47.250 --> 00:34:48.270 align:middle line:90%
You could do gardening.

00:34:48.270 --> 00:34:49.320 align:middle line:90%
You could do surfing.

00:34:49.320 --> 00:34:54.239 align:middle line:84%
You could do whatever
allows you to just go inward

00:34:54.239 --> 00:34:57.970 align:middle line:84%
and to feel that
juicy bliss spot.

00:34:57.970 --> 00:34:58.770 align:middle line:90%
And we all know it.

00:34:58.770 --> 00:35:00.330 align:middle line:90%
We've all felt it.

00:35:00.330 --> 00:35:04.890 align:middle line:84%
So cultivating some sort of
meditation practice, for me,

00:35:04.890 --> 00:35:07.240 align:middle line:84%
it's the first thing I
do as soon as I wake up.

00:35:07.240 --> 00:35:09.320 align:middle line:84%
I do 20 minutes in the
morning and 20 minutes

00:35:09.320 --> 00:35:10.760 align:middle line:90%
in the afternoon.

00:35:10.760 --> 00:35:12.770 align:middle line:90%
And that really helps me.

00:35:12.770 --> 00:35:16.160 align:middle line:84%
It helps with anxiety,
overwhelmed, stress,

00:35:16.160 --> 00:35:17.790 align:middle line:90%
all those sorts of things.

00:35:17.790 --> 00:35:21.650 align:middle line:84%
So for me, that has been
imperative because your ego

00:35:21.650 --> 00:35:24.340 align:middle line:84%
cannot live in the
present moment.

00:35:24.340 --> 00:35:27.440 align:middle line:84%
Your ego is there
when you're stressing

00:35:27.440 --> 00:35:31.380 align:middle line:84%
over the past and
anxious about the future.

00:35:31.380 --> 00:35:33.350 align:middle line:84%
So when you're in the
past or the future,

00:35:33.350 --> 00:35:35.150 align:middle line:84%
that's when your
mean girl comes in.

00:35:35.150 --> 00:35:36.917 align:middle line:84%
Your ego plants all
these seeds of doubts.

00:35:36.917 --> 00:35:38.000 align:middle line:90%
You should have done this.

00:35:38.000 --> 00:35:38.720 align:middle line:90%
You're not good enough.

00:35:38.720 --> 00:35:39.827 align:middle line:90%
You're not smart enough.

00:35:39.827 --> 00:35:40.910 align:middle line:90%
You should have said this.

00:35:40.910 --> 00:35:42.020 align:middle line:90%
You haven't done this.

00:35:42.020 --> 00:35:45.530 align:middle line:84%
But when you're present,
you're in the moment,

00:35:45.530 --> 00:35:48.710 align:middle line:84%
